The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Quick takes
                                                                                                                       7                                      Quick takes
                            
	Now Pazzini blasts ball  
	Sestriere: Italy striker Giampaolo Pazzini says the World Cup ball is a disaster. Italys players have been training with the Adidas ball at their training camp in the Italian Alps in a bid to become accustomed to it.  
	The Sampdoria striker said on Saturday: The balls are a disaster, both for goalkeepers and attackers. On Friday, Brazil goalkeeper Julio Cesar called the Adidas ball horrible and terrible.               
	Evra ready  
	Paris: Defender Patrice Evra has already captained Manchester United to victory this season and is now ready to lead France at the World Cup if Thierry Henry doesnt win back his starting place.  
	Evra wore the France armband for the first time on Wednesday night against Costa Rica. Its hugely satisfying to be France captain When I am in the changing rooms, its great to see that the guys are behind me and proud of me, Evra said.               
	Samba in US  
	New York: The United States will host Brazil in a friendly on August 10 at the New Meadowlands Stadium in East Rutherford, less than a month after the World Cup in South Africa. It will be the first appearance by five-times world champions Brazil in New York in 14 years, the US Soccer Federation said on Friday.  
	Blatter boost  
	Polokwane: South Africas recent form has improved the chances of the host nation advancing to the second round of the World Cup, Fifa president Sepp Blatter said on Saturday. They are on the right way, the right way to go to the next round, Blatter said.  
	Karhan out  
	Bratislava: Slovakia midfielder Miroslav Karhan was ruled out of the World Cup on Saturday after failing to recover from a hamstring problem, local news agency SITA reported. I have a little rupture there, preventing me from starting in the World Cup finals. There are two weeks to go to the finals but I should take a break for three weeks, said Karhan, Slovakias most-capped player with 96 starts.   AGENCIES                                                                                                                 
